China’s Biggest Coal-to-Chemical Plant Starts Up, Xinhua Says

-- B y   A n n   K o h
-- 
2011-05-06T02:19:23Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-06/china-s-biggest-coal-to-chemical-plant-starts-up-xinhua-says.html
China ’s biggest coal-to-chemical plant
has begun operations, Xinhua news agency reported today.  The facility is owned by a unit of Shenhua Group Corp. and
has a capacity to make 500,000 metric tons a year of
polypropylene, 41,200 tons a year of liquefied fuel and other
byproducts, Xinhua said, citing a statement from the subsidiary
company. The plant is located in northwestern Ningxia province,
according to the report.  To contact the reporter on this story:
